14 Sec. 31. 1. If the district court appoints a receiver for a substandard
15 property pursuant to section 29 of this act, the owner of the substandard property,
16 and any agent or employee of the owner, shall not collect rent from any tenant,
17 interfere with the receiver in the operation of the substandard property or
18 encumber or transfer any interest in the substandard property.
19 2. Unless otherwise ordered by the district court, a receiver for a
20 substandard property shall:
21 (a) Take full and complete control of the substandard property.
22 (b) Manage the substandard property and pay any expenses of the operation
23 of the substandard property, including, without limitation, paying the taxes,
